s' relationships with geography, food, and society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aClimatic changes. 0aUrban ecology (Biology). 0aUrban geography. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geography.2bisacsh1 aReba, Meredith, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSullivan, Kathryn D.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300241082?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300241082423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300241082/original  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles